<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title><%= pageTitle %> – Art of the Orient</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <%- include('partials/header', { headerClass, pageTitle }) %>
  <%- include('partials/page-wrap-start') %>
  <main class="main">
    <h2 class="gallery-title"><%= pageTitle %></h2>
    <section class="section-text section-text-full">
      <p>Bulhwa (불화), or Buddhist painting, encompasses the devotional and ritual art produced for Korean temples and believers over many centuries. Ranging from large altar pieces and paradise scenes to portraits of monks and protective deities, Bulhwa combines precise iconography with rich color and gold, serving both worship and instruction. The tradition reflects the deep influence of Buddhism on Korean culture and the skill of monastic and professional painters who sustained it.</p>
    </section>
  </main>
  <%- include('partials/page-wrap-end') %>
  <script src="/js/nav.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
